<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1899-04-14T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1899-04-14T00:00:00-05:00" n="610" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d610">
                        <head><hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Hay</persName> to Mr.
                                    <persName type="to">Choate</persName>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1899-04-14"><hi rend="italic">April 14,
                                1899</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p>Agreement for Samoan commission reached on basis of Lord Salisbury’s
                            recent identical telegrams to British ambassadors in Washington and
                            Berlin. To be completed by exchange of notes at London. You will at once
                            arrange with Lord Salisbury and address him a formal note accepting on
                            behalf of the Government of the United States the joint agreement in the
                            words of Lord Salisbury’s telegrams.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Hay.</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>